                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 1rb: Recipe for a medication.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The name of the medication is erased; written by well-trained hand.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 1v-2r (in black ink, above), 2v-3ra (below): Hymn to St. George.</span></span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Crudely written, in the same hand as Additiones 5-7, 12, 15. The same hymn is contained in SM-011 (fols. 163v-164r).</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 1v-2r (in reddish brown ink), 3v-4r (above) and 4rb, 5r (above, in reddish-brown ink): Hymn(s) to the Virgin Mary.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Crudely written, in the same hand as Additiones 4, 6, 7, 12, 15.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 3r-v, 4ra: </span><span style="line-height: 115%; color: black">List of the church feasts.</span></span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Crudely written, by the same hand as additiones 4, 5, 7, 12, 15.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 4v: Excerpt from </span><span style="line-height: 115%; color: black">M&#228;lk&#477;&#704;a G&#228;br&#228; M&#228;nf&#228;s Q&#601;ddus (&#8220;Image of G&#228;br&#228; M&#228;nf&#228;s Q&#601;ddus&#8221;).</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Crudely written in black and reddish-brown ink, in the same hand as Additiones 4-6, 12, 15.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 5v (in the lower margin): Excerpt from </span><span style="line-height: 115%; color: black">M&#228;lk&#477;&#704;a </span><span style="line-height: 115%; color: black">&#704;</span><span style="line-height: 115%; color: black">Edom (&#8220;Image of Paradise&#8221;).</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Written in a poor hand; some parts of the text are hardly legible because the ink has faded away.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a9">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 21va-30rb (in the lower margin): Unidentified hymn to the Virgin Mary. </span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Some parts of the text are hardly legible because the ink has faded away; probably written in more than one hand.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a10">
                           <locus/><div style="line-height: normal"><span style="font-size: small">Fol. 95vb: Note on the arrival of two unnamed metropolitans to Ethiopia.</span></div><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 95vb:</span></span><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%"> </span></span><span style="font-size: large"><span style="line-height: 115%">&#4704;&#4829;&#4757;&#4721;&#4961; &#4824;&#4632;&#4757;&#4961; &#4632;&#4925;&#4769;&#4961; &#4970;&#4961; &#4915;&#4915;&#4659;&#4725;&#4961; &#4969;&#4961; &#4704;&#4848;&#4757;&#4779;&#4620;&#4961; &#4808;&#4969;&#4961; &#4704;&#4661;&#4755;&#4653;&#4961; &#4824;&#4632;&#4925;&#4768;&#4961;&#160;&#4704;&#4661;&#4755;&#4653;&#4961; &#4720;&#4656;&#4845;&#4632;&#160;</span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"><p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 95vb: In this year came two metropolitans, one by D&#228;nkale and one by S&#601;nnar. The one who came by S&#601;nnar was appointed. </span></span></p></q>
                           <p>Carefully written in a good hand.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a11">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 120v-121ra: Register of lucky and unlucky days in each month of the year.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Written in a mediocre hand.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a12">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 121ra-b, 121va: Protective prayers against abdominal pains, snake bites and the evil eye. </span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Crudely written, in the same hand as Additiones 4-7, 15.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a13">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 219r-v: Unidentified text concerning the history of the Near and Middle East under the Turkish rule.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Carefully written. The text may be a piece from the second part of the “History of Wäldä ʿAmid” concerning the history of Islam.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a14">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 218v (below), 219r (below): Magic recipe and a protective prayer.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Crudely written in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a15">
                           <locus/><div style="line-height: normal"><span style="font-size: small">Fols. 219va-b (below), 220ra: Excerpt from M&#228;lk&#601;&#704;a Giyorgis (&#8220;Image of Giyorgis&#8221;).</span></div><q xml:lang="gez"><p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 219va:</span></span><span style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt"> </span><span style="font-size: large"><span style="line-height: 115%">&#4774;&#4961; &#4941;&#4897;&#4752;&#4961; &#4648;&#4853;&#4772;&#4725;&#4961; &#4773;&#4637;&#4649;&#4920;&#4720;&#4961; &#4752;&#4939;&#4661;&#4961; &#4808;&#4819;&#4813;&#4622;</span></span><span style="font-size: large"><span style="line-height: 115%"><span style="font-size: large"><span style="line-height: 115%">&#4961;</span></span>&#8230;</span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Crudely written, in the same hand as Additiones 4-7, 12.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a16">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 220rb: Unidentified text about how Adam and Eve farmed the land. </span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Written in a fine hand.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a17">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 220v (in the upper margin): Instruction on how to use the protective prayer.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Written in a fine hand.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a18">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 220v (below addition 16): Protective prayer.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Written in a fine hand.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a19">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fol. 220vb, 221ra-221va: Prayer against &#7717;&#601;mam&#228; w&#601;g</span><span style="line-height: 115%">&#704;</span><span style="line-height: 115%">at (rheumatism?). </span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Written in a fine hand.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a20">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="line-height: 115%">Fols. 221va: Three protective prayers.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Crudely written in various hands.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fol. 1r: The titles “Säʿatat”, “Tarik zä-Wäldä ʿAmid” and the local shelf mark of the Ms. “420” are written in black big letters, in Tǝgrǝñña. &#xD;
- The closing part of Text I is written twice, in fols. 77 (by hand b) and 78 (by hand a). &#xD;
- Fol. 220v: Two hardly legible texts written in faded reddish-brown and black ink. &#xD;
- Initial letters of the sections of Text II, indicating the day on which the new year begins, are rewritten in smaller size to the left site.&#xD;
- Traces of an erased text in fol. 146vb (7 lines) and fol. 147ra (3 lines).&#xD;
- Fols. 1r, 3r, 4v, 7v, 94v, 221vb: Minor notes, writing exercises, crude drawings, doodles.</item>
